  "text": "Assumptions 1-3 are sufficient conditions for strong duality to hold, and for an optimal primal-dual pair (x , λ ) to exists, where x = [x 1 · · · x m ] . Moreover, for any optimal pair (x , λ ) the Saddle-Point Theorem [CITATION_1] holds, i.e.,",
